data.content:
## What Breaks in .NET 11

In .NET 10, the EF Core Cosmos DB provider deprecated sync-over-async and made it **opt-in**. In .NET 11, that opt-in is **removed entirely**. The sync APIs now throw `InvalidOperationException`.

Every call in your repository — `ToList()`, `First()`, `Count()`, `SaveChanges()` — will fail at runtime.

### The Fix: Convert to Async

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

**Key changes:**
- Return types become `Task<T>` / `Task`
- Methods are marked `async` and use `await`
- LINQ terminals → async variants (`ToListAsync`, `FirstAsync`, `CountAsync`)
- `SaveChanges()` → `SaveChangesAsync()`
- Remove the old `EnableSyncOverAsync()` Cosmos configuration — it's no longer recognized

**Note:** This is async all the way up — callers must also be updated to `await` these methods, propagating `async` through the call chain.
